or><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>2023-10-04</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Started to work on proving the “dream initial algebra theorem” in <link href="jms-009S.xml" type="local" title="Strong impredicative encodings">strong impredicative encodings</link>; managed to bang out the structure identity principle for homomorphisms of <tex>F</tex>-algebras. I have almost defined the wild category of <tex>F</tex>-algebras; I needed to include data in the “endofunctor” witnessing preservation of unitors and associators.</p><p>First <link href="jms-00A6.xml" type="local" title="Wednesday Meeting">Wednesday Meeting</link> at the <link href="camcl.xml" type="local" title="Cambridge Computer Laboratory">Cambridge Computer Laboratory</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>